cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.SE. 

This paper involves the use of deep reinforcement learning and natural language processing techniques to train agents to play text-adventure games. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves the use of knowledge graphs as a representation for domain knowledge transfer, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SD (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper involves testing the methods across multiple games, which falls under cs.SE (Software Engineering).
